-3- The effect of calling any member function other than the destructor, the move-assignment operator, or
valid()the member functions get, wait, wait_for, or 
wait_until on a shared_future object for which valid() == false is undefined. 
[Note: Implementations are encouraged to detect this case and throw an object of type 
future_error with an error condition of future_errc::no_state. — end note]


